  "texts": [
    "In software based ANNs, this is not a challenge.",
    "However, the available inputs in hardware ANNs are limited by the maximal size of the memristor crossbar.",
    "In the literature, such a challenge has been tackled considering different approaches: For instance, given the MNIST dataset in which images have a resolution of 28 × 28 pixels one option is to implement the synaptic layer using multiple crossbars to fit the 784 inputs (e.g., 13 64 × 64 or 4 256 × 256 crossbars would be needed 93).",
    "However, for research efforts focused on the device level, this is usually out of reach as requires a nonstraightforward CMOSmemristor integration.",
    "Another option is to consider more complex neural networks, such as the convolutional neural networks (CNN) 55."
  ],
